{{Taxobox | name = Anaspididae | regnum = [[Animal]]ia | phylum = [[Arthropod]]a | subphylum = [[Crustacean|Crustacea]] | classis = [[Malacostraca]] | superordo = [[Syncarida]] | ordo = [[Anaspidacea]] | familia = '''Anaspididae''' | familia_authority = [[George M. Thomson|Thomson]], 1893 | subdivision_ranks = Genera | subdivision = *''Allanaspides'' <small>Swain, Wilson, Hickman & Ong, 1970 </small> *''Anaspides'' <small>Thomson, 1894</small> *''Paranaspides'' <small>Smith, 1908</small> }}
'''Anaspididae''' is a [[family (biology)|family]] of freshwater [[crustacean]] that is endemic to [[Tasmania]], [[Australia]].<ref name="Lowry">{{cite web |author=J. K. Lowry |author2=M. Yerman |last-author-amp=yes |date=October 2, 2002 |url=http://crustacea.net/crustace/anaspidacea/www/anaspid.htm |title=Anaspidacea: Families |accessdate=April 15, 2010}}</ref> The family contains 3 [[genus|genera]] and 5 [[species]]. This group of crustaceans are considered [[living fossil]]s.<ref name="Lowry"/> They are commonly and collectively known as the '''Tasmanian anaspid crustaceans'''. Anaspidids have stalked eyes, long antennae and [[antennule]]s, and a slender body with no carapace. The two species of ''Allanaspides''<ref>{{Cite journal | author = Inland Water Crustacean Specialist Group | title = ''Allanaspides hickmani'' | journal = [[The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species]] | volume = 1996 | page = e.T863A13086271 | publisher = [[IUCN]] | date = 1996 | url = http://www.iucnredlist.org/details/863/0 | doi = 10.2305/IUCN.UK.1996.RLTS.T863A13086271.en | access-date = 27 December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | author = Inland Water Crustacean Specialist Group | title = ''Allanaspides helonomus'' | journal = [[The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species]] | volume = 1996 | page = e.T862A13086150 | publisher = [[IUCN]] | date = 1996 | url = http://www.iucnredlist.org/details/862/0 | doi = 10.2305/IUCN.UK.1996.RLTS.T862A13086150.en | access-date = 27 December 2017}}</ref> and the single species of ''Paranaspides''<ref>{{Cite journal | author = Inland Water Crustacean Specialist Group | title = ''Paranaspides lacustris'' | journal = [[The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species]] | volume = 1996 | page = e.T16137A5408118 | publisher = [[IUCN]] | date = 1996 | url = http://www.iucnredlist.org/details/16137/0 | doi = 10.2305/IUCN.UK.1996.RLTS.T16137A5408118.en | access-date = 27 December 2017}}</ref> are all listed as [[vulnerable species|vulnerable]] on the [[IUCN Red List]].
==Taxonomy== *'''''Allanaspides''''' <small>Swain, Wilson, Hickman & Ong, 1970 </small> **''[[Allanaspides hickmani]]'' <small>Swain, Wilson & Ong, 1970</small> – commonly known as Hickman's pygmy mountain shrimp **''[[Allanaspides helonomus]]'' <small>Swain, Wilson, Hickman & Ong, 1970</small> *'''''Anaspides''''' <small>Thomson, 1894</small> **''[[Anaspides tasmaniae]]'' <small>Thomson, 1892</small> **''[[Anaspides spinulae]]'' <small>Williams, 1965</small> *'''''Paranaspides''''' <small>Smith, 1908</small> **''[[Paranaspides|Paranaspides lacustris]]'' <small>Smith, 1909</small>
